<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>

<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

<title>Publications Library | PanorOmics</title>

<style>

*{
  margin:0;
  padding:0;
  box-sizing:border-box;
}

body{
  background:#020817;
  color:white;
  font-family:Inter,sans-serif;
}

.container{
  max-width:1200px;
  margin:auto;
  padding:80px 7% 60px;
}

.back{
  color:#3b82f6;
  text-decoration:none;
  font-size:.9rem;
  font-weight:700;
}

.hero{
  margin-top:32px;
  text-align:center;
}

.library-logo{
  width:140px;
  height:auto;
  display:block;
  margin:0 auto 24px;
}

.hero h1{
  font-size:clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4.5rem);
  line-height:.95;
  letter-spacing:-.05em;
  margin-bottom:18px;
}

.hero h1 span{
  color:#3b82f6;
}

.hero p{
  color:#cbd5e1;
  font-size:1rem;
  line-height:1.8;
  max-width:900px;
  margin:0 auto;
}

.section{
  margin-top:60px;
}

.section h2{
  font-size:2rem;
  margin-bottom:16px;
}

.section h2 span{
  color:#3b82f6;
}

.section p{
  color:#cbd5e1;
  line-height:1.9;
  font-size:1rem;
  margin-bottom:16px;
}

.categories{
  display:grid;
  grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(260px,1fr));
  gap:20px;
  margin-top:24px;
}

.card{
  background:rgba(8,15,35,.75);
  border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.12);
  border-radius:18px;
  padding:24px;
  transition:.3s ease;
}

.card:hover{
  border-color:#3b82f6;
  transform:translateY(-4px);
}

.card h3{
  color:#3b82f6;
  margin-bottom:10px;
}

.card p{
  margin:0;
  font-size:.92rem;
}

.hero-button{
  display:inline-flex;
  align-items:center;
  justify-content:center;
  margin-top:24px;
  padding:12px 24px;
  border-radius:999px;
  background:#2563eb;
  color:white;
  text-decoration:none;
  font-weight:700;
}

</style>

</head>

<body>

<div class="container">

<a href="/" class="back">
← Back to PanorOmics
</a>

<section class="hero">

<img
  src="/panoromics-logo.png"
  alt="PanorOmics Logo"
  class="library-logo"
/>

<h1>
Publications <span>Library</span>
</h1>

<p>
The PanorOmics Publications Library provides curated scientific literature,
research highlights, landmark discoveries, and educational resources across
omics sciences, biotechnology, artificial intelligence, systems biology,
and precision medicine.
</p>

</section>

<section class="section">

<h2>
Browse by <span>Omics Science</span>
</h2>

<div class="categories">

<div class="card">
<h3>Genomics</h3>
<p>Genome sequencing, genetic variation, precision medicine, and population genomics.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Transcriptomics</h3>
<p>RNA expression, RNA sequencing, non-coding RNA, and gene regulation.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Proteomics</h3>
<p>Protein expression, signaling pathways, biomarkers, and systems proteomics.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Metabolomics</h3>
<p>Metabolic pathways, biochemical phenotypes, and disease-associated metabolites.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Lipidomics</h3>
<p>Lipid signaling, membrane biology, inflammation, and metabolic regulation.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Epigenomics</h3>
<p>DNA methylation, chromatin biology, histone modifications, and gene regulation.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Microbiomics</h3>
<p>Microbial ecosystems, host interactions, microbiome therapeutics, and environmental microbiology.</p>
</div>

</div>

</section>

<section class="section">

<h2>
Browse by <span>Research Area</span>
</h2>

<div class="categories">

<div class="card">
<h3>Cancer Biology</h3>
<p>Genomic, epigenomic, transcriptomic, and multi-omics approaches to cancer research.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Precision Medicine</h3>
<p>Personalized diagnostics, therapeutics, and predictive biomarkers.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Artificial Intelligence</h3>
<p>Machine learning, computational biology, and AI-driven biomedical discovery.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Biotechnology</h3>
<p>Translational science, innovation, therapeutics, and emerging technologies.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Systems Biology</h3>
<p>Integrating biological networks across molecular and clinical scales.</p>
</div>

<div class="card">
<h3>Omics Sciences</h3>
<p>Theoretical foundations, interdisciplinary integration, and the Architecture of Life.</p>
</div>

</div>

</section>

<section class="section">

